{
  "stem": "23438.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was terrified every time she'd gone out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She wouldn't let me go with her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Somehow we survived Warsaw bombardment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We'd survive, later, a lot worse bombardments.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then we thought it was the end of the world.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But obviously it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Then we moved into my aunt's flat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the bombardment became even heavier and worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But that was only two or three days, and then eerie quiet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The city had surrendered.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We also had, during the siege, continuous soldiers going through.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The retreating army, they were dirty, with terrible shoes falling off their feet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They were hungry and thirsty and often wounded.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we had to help them, wash them, maybe then give them some water.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was really sort of a difficult time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But by, I think, the 26 September, it was all over.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The first-- the first siege, the first bombardment of the war was finished.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Then we went back to our flat in Mokotowska.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] About a month later, my uncle, Anna's husband, in Lodz, he was a member of the Bund.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He was a city councilor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He was arrested in October in the first group of hostages in Lodz, and shot soon after, executed soon after.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then my aunt and grandma, who lived the last few years before the war in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And aunt's two children-- Alina, who was my senior of about four years, and [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Jannick ?] who was my junior of a year and a half-- came to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they moved into our flat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was a terrible winter, that first war winter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was exceedingly cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There was no coal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "There was no way of heating the flat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "There was little food.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We had not all that much money.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
